node.title: Graphic objects
node.description:
With graphic objects we can communicate more complex messages.
The graphic objects relates to our illustration but are often one single object. We can explain events, products, situations and environments.

node.title: Icons
node.description:
We want our icons to be informative and easy to understand.
The icons are less abstract and more specific then the graphic objects. They should support the textual information or cluster information.
The icons come in various sizes, Each size with variations of details.

node.title: Illustration
node.description:
With illustrations we can communicate our brand idea. We are local.
We can illustrate geographic differences between our Länsbolag. We can also communicate different branches within Länsförsäkringar in a playful way. Often used as decoration.

node.title: Graphs and when to use them
Templates Lansforsakringar.se
node.description: Sidmallar för länsförsäkringar.se med syfte och information om varje sidtyp.

node.title: Brand
node.description:
Länsförsäkringar är ett av Sveriges mest kända varumärken. Vår symbol ritades 1969 av den grafiska formgivaren Hans Hug och är idag en av Sveriges mest kända företagssymboler. 
Det är något vi värnar om tillsammans.

node.title: Design hörnstenar
node.description: För att efterlikna det personliga mötet ska vi använda oss av våra hörnstenar. Expertis, labba och kontroll.

node.title: Designer
node.description: Som Designer i Länsförsäkringsgruppen finns det lite delar som du behöver veta innan du börjar designa. Vi går igenom allt här.

node.title: Webbtillgänglighet förklaringar checklistan
node.description: Här går vi igenom punkt för punkt vad de betyder för Länsförsäkringar att följa checklistorna.

node.title: Headings
node.description: We have two types of headlines - normal headings and hero display headings.

node.title: Lists
node.description: Use to list small texts in dots or in numerical order and break up large blocks of text and make important info stand out.

node.title: Avatar
node.description: Avatars are used to give a visual representations of the various parties involved in a conversation.

node.title: Paragraph
node.description: Brödtexten används på alla ställen där man inte vill ha en rubrik eller fet text.

node.title: Lead paragraph
node.description: The lead paragraph is placed first on a page and is used to summarise the contents of a page.

node.title: Progress bar
node.description: The progress bar helps the user in understanding how much of a flow has been completed if there is much to do in the flow.

node.title: Alert
node.description: Alerts are used to provide (contextual) messages for typical user actions and for important communication from Länsförsäkringar of a non-commercial nature.

node.title: Timeline
node.description: The timeline component is an interactive way for the user to follow the progress of an (ongoing) errand, such as a damage claim or loan application.

node.title: Spinner
node.description: The spinner is used to show that the system is loading/fetching data and that the response isn't instantaneous.

node.title: Collapse
node.description: Lets the user expand the current page and displays examples or a longer explanation which support the user in performing their task. This is the most common way of showing Read more in relation to forms.

node.title: Modal
node.description: Modals are triggered by the user clicking a button. They have two use cases; in a “Read more”-context and signing stuff.

node.title: Popover Tooltip
node.description: Used primarily as an explanation of terms and difficult words in inline text. When the user clicks/hovers a word with a popover tooltip a small popover appears in which explanatory text is displayed.

node.title: Callout
node.description: The callout is used to highlight information which we want the user to notice in relation to a chunk of text.

node.title: Panel
node.description: Panels are our standard containers when we want to “box in” content. When panels are used the whole page is usually divided into different panels.

node.title: Card
node.description: The card component is used to inform users about related products or content.

node.title: Line element
node.description: The line element is used to separate parts of the page from each other.

node.title: Price Box
node.description: The Price-box component displays the price/cost in a sidebar (desktop)/at the bottom of the screen (mobile) in flows where the user can purchase/sign-up for something. The price is updated as the user makes various choices in the main flow.

node.title: Breadcrumbs
node.description: Breadcrumbs lets the user get a sense of where they are in your application and offers a way back up in the site tree.

node.title: Value Box
node.description: The value box is intended to draw the users attention and for them to at-a-glance see the total value of the related content. It is primarily used in Mina sidor to display value of total/specific content.

node.title: Tables
node.description: Tables are used to display data. The data can be either of an informative nature or comparative.

node.title: Navbar
node.description: The navbar is the foundation for the various menus used at Länsförsäkringar.

node.title: Tabs
node.description: Tabs are used as contextual navigation when the user has landed on a page which hasn't any submenues in the main navigation.

node.title: Pagination
node.description: Use pagination to let the user where they are in a flow consisting of several pages.

node.title: Checkbox
node.description: Your standard web component dressed in a Länsförsäkringar styling.

node.title: Datepicker
node.description: The datepicker is the input field used when a date is the expected input.

node.title: Radio buttons
node.description: There are three types of radio buttons in LFUI; standard radio buttons, button groups and radio cards.

node.title: Input field
node.description: Input fields are fields in which the user can enter text of some type (be it letters or numbers).

node.title: Dropdown
node.description: The dropdown provides the user with given options in a list which expands over the webpage when the user clicks on the container.

node.title: Bar charts
node.description: Bar charts presents data in proportion to the values they represent. You can compare either various data sources for the same time period or the same data source over several different time spans. A typical use case at Länsförsäkringar is to compare the development of a fund or stock between various years.

node.title: Upload
node.description: Use this component if you want to let your user upload a file to us.

node.title: Slider
node.description: A slider provides a visual way of providing a value.

node.title: Donut Chart
node.description: Donut charts are best to use when you are trying to compare parts of a whole. They do not show changes over time.

node.title: Line chart
node.description: Line charts are used to display changes over a period of time. Line charts can also be used to compare changes over the same period of time for different data sets.

node.title: X-Y Plot
node.description: X-Y plots are used to determine relationships between the two different things.

node.title: Distribution bar
node.description: The distribution bar gives the user an overview of the relative size of different values in relation to each other, like the different funds in your ISK.

node.title: Map Chart
node.description: Use a map if you have data with a geographical component. The typical use case is to show where in the world investments are placed.

node.title: Buttons
node.description: Buttons are used as a part of a flow, and is the component which the user clicks to make progress in said flow.

node.title: Links
node.description: Links are used when we want to guide the user away from the current page, as we expect them to want information which isn't part of the current flow.

node.title: Shortcuts
node.description: The shortcut is preferably used at the top of a page to draw the users attention to another page or section.
